CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F318A1777986670
OL,3,CFood prices set to rise by 50% on
OL,4,Cstart of cost-of-living crisis by
OL,5,CNovember
OL,7,FAccording to the analysis, the cost of
OL,8,Fstaples including pasta, frozen
OL,9,Fvegetables, chocolate, eggs and beef `
OL,10,Fall up between 50% and 64% ` and olive
OL,11,Foil, up 113%, had already seen some of
OL,12,Fthe steepest rises, reflecting their
OL,13,Fsensitivity to volatile oil and gas
OL,14,Fprices, synthetic fertiliser costs and
OL,15,Fclimate impacts such as droughts,
OL,16,Ffloods, and heatwaves, both in the UK
OL,17,Fand in key import regions.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G3/11
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,319,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31804
SC,0004
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F318A1777986670
OL,3,CFood prices set to rise by 50% on
OL,4,Cstart of cost-of-living crisis by
OL,5,CNovember
OL,7,FTogether, these forces had pushed
OL,8,Fhousehold food bills up by an average
OL,9,Fof #605 over 2022 and 2023, with
OL,10,Fenergy shocks accounting for #244 of
OL,11,Fthis, the ECIU said.
OL,13,FMore recently, five climate-impacted
OL,14,Ffoods ` butter, milk, beef, chocolate
OL,15,Fand coffee ` had been responsible for
OL,16,Fmuch of the continued pressure on food
OL,17,Finflation, with the price of these
OL,18,Ffoods rising over four times faster
OL,19,Fthan other food and drink.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G4/11
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
