PN,31809
SC,0009
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F318A1777986670
OL,3,CFood prices set to rise by 50% on
OL,4,Cstart of cost-of-living crisis by
OL,5,CNovember
OL,7,FLatest inflation figures from
OL,8,FWorldpanel by Numerator show grocery
OL,9,Fprices are currently 3.8% higher than
OL,10,Fa year ago, with households warned
OL,11,Fthat the Middle East conflict has "not
OL,12,Fyet" filtered through to supermarket
OL,13,Fshelves.
OL,15,FAs consumers adapt to higher prices,
OL,16,Fdata from the Waste and Resources
OL,17,FAction Programme (Wrap) suggest that
OL,18,Fself-reported waste of the four key
OL,19,Fproducts ` bread, milk, chicken, and
OL,20,Fpotatoes ` has fallen from 21% to
OL,21,F18.8% since 2024.
OL,26,@sD@cOUtD@DO]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G9/11
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
